@REM --------
@node "Registration"
@title "ViewDiz - Free Registration."
@{b}@{u}Free Registration:@{ub}@{uu}

You have now got a once-in-a-lifetime chance to register ViewDiz free of
charge! Just run the included registration-script and follow the instructions.

I'm offering this because I'd like some feedback from you guys - new features,
suggestions, bugs (?) etc.
In return you'll get on the ViewDiz mailing list, and recieve an email each
time a new version is available.

Thanks in advance, @{"Mikael Lund" link author}
@endnode
@REM --------
@node Extern
@title "External Modules & Wizards for ViewDiz."
@{b}@{u}Filetype Modules:@{ub}@{uu}

ViewDiz recognizes filetypes using external modules. This is an examination of
the available modules - what they do and what they require.

  Archives:   @{"Lha" link mod 35}, @{"Lzx" link mod 47}, @{"Arj" link mod 1}, @{"Zip" link mod 146}, @{"UUe" link mod 135}, @{"Tar" link mod 183}, @{"Tgz" link mod 195}
  Diskimages: @{"xFX" link mod 157}, @{"DMS" link mod 11}
  Packers:    @{"xPK" link mod 169}, @{"GZip" link mod 218}, @{"Exe" link mod 207}
  Music:      @{"Mod" link mod 60}, @{"Mus" link mod 87}, @{"Mp3" link mod 75}
  Text:       @{"Txt" link mod 122}, @{"Htm" link mod 23}, @{"Readme" link mod 111}
  Graphics    @{"Pic" link mod 100}


@{b}@{u}Wizards:@{ub}@{uu}

ViewDiz can use external 'wizards' that can do something with the current file
or description. This is an explanation of the various wizards that comes with
the ViewDiz package.

  @{"Banner" link banner}
  @{"Clip" link clip}
  @{"Delreadme" link delreadme}
  @{"Guidelist" link guidelist}
  @{"Log" link Log}
  @{"Strip" link strip}
  @{"Wrap" link wrap}
@endnode
;---------
@node "Mod"
@{b}Arj@{ub}

FILETYPE:	Arj-packed archive.
PATTERN:	#?.arj
PROPERTIES:	Read, execute
DESCRIPTION:	file_id.diz
EXECUTE:	Unpack archive.
REQUIRES:	UnArj_FID, UnArj (unpacking only)
AUTHOR:		Mikael Lund
NOTES:

@{b}DMS@{ub}

FILETYPE:	DiskMasher disk-images.
PATTERN:	(#?.dms)
PROPERTIES:	Read, Write, Delete, Execute
DESCRIPTION:	File_ID.DIZ
EXECUTE:	Unpack to a device, selected by user.
REQUIRES:	C:DMSdescript by Remo/Mystic-DeSign
		C:DMS & C:RequestChoice (Unpacking, only)
AUTHOR:		Mikael Lund
NOTES:		Edit the script to change the devices.

@{b}Htm@{ub}

FILETYPE:	HTML-documents
PATTERN:	(#?.html|#?.htm)
PROPERTIES:	Read, Execute
DESCRIPTION:	Document <title>
EXECUTE:	View document.
REQUIRES:	Rexxmast running.
		SYS:Utilities/MoreHTML/MoreHTML (for viewing)
AUTHOR:		Mikael Lund
NOTES:

@{b}Lha@{ub}

FILETYPE:	Lha/Lzh archives.
PATTERN:	(#?.lha|#?.lzh)
PROPERTIES:	Read, Write, Delete, Execute
DESCRIPTION:	File_ID.DIZ, Aminet.readme
EXECUTE:	Unpack archive; requester asks for destination.
REQUIRES:	C:Lha, C:Requestfile (WB39+)
		Env:ViewDiz/Modules/Readme
AUTHOR:		Mikael Lund
NOTES:		Speed up with "C:Resident C:Lha pure"

@{b}Lzx@{ub}

FILETYPE:	Lzx archives.
PATTERN:	(#?.lzx)
PROPERTIES:	Read, Write, Delete, Execute
DESCRIPTION:	File_ID.DIZ
EXECUTE:	Unpack archive; requester asks for destination.
REQUIRES:	C:Lzx, C:Requestfile (WB39+)
AUTHOR:		Mikael Lund
NOTES:		Speed up with "C:Resident C:Lzx pure". The keyfile
		for "Lzx" can be found on the aminet - this will
                increase processing speed.

@{b}Mod@{ub}

FILETYPE:	Protracker-, MED- & OctaMED modules
PATTERN:	(mod.#?|med.#?)
PROPERTIES:	Read, Write, Delete, Execute
DESCRIPTION:	File_ID.DIZ / Filenote
EXECUTE:	Send music to player - Eagleplayer, delitracker, Amodplay,
		Hippoplayer etc. If one of these isn't open, it will try
		to do so.
REQUIRES:	C:ModuleDescript by Charlie/KF
		Env:viewdiz/modules/mus (for playing)
		Env:viewdiz/modules/xpk (if xpk-packed)
AUTHOR:		Mikael Lund
NOTES:		Edit the "mus"-modules if you want to change player.

@{b}Mp3@{ub}

FILETYPE:	MPEG-3 packed audio.
PATTERN:	(#?.mp3|#?.mpeg3)
PROPERTIES:	Read, Execute
DESCRIPTION:	MP3 Tags.
EXECUTE:	Try and play the file.
REQUIRES:	MP3Info by Thorvald Natvig
		ENV:ViewDiz/Modules/Mus (for playing)
AUTHOR:		Mikael Lund
NOTES:		

@{b}Mus@{ub}

FILETYPE:	Non-tracker music => Exotic music.
PATTERN:	(ft.#?|ft2.#?|s3m.#?|thx.#?|psid.#?|aon.#?|ml.#?|dw.#?|hip.#?|mdat.#?)
PROPERTIES:	Read, write, delete, execute
DESCRIPTION:	file_id.diz / filenote
EXECUTE:	Play music
REQUIRES:	Env:ViewDiz/Modules/Xpk (for xPK-packed tunes)
		PlayTune v1.0+ (for playing)
AUTHOR:		Mikael Lund
NOTES:		xPK packed tunes can hold a file_id.diz otherwize the filenote
		will be used.

@{b}Pic@{ub}

FILETYPE:	Graphics
PATTERN:	(#?.gif|#?.iff|#?.jpg|#?.jpeg|#?.ilbm)
PROPERTIES:	Read, write, delete, execute
DESCRIPTION:	file_id.diz
EXECUTE:	View picture using Multiview or DOpus5+
REQUIRES:	MagicDIZ v2+ by Icarus/Hellfire
AUTHOR:		Mikael Lund
NOTES:

@{b}Readme@{ub}

FILETYPE:	Aminet readme
PATTERN:	#?.readme
PROPERTIES:	Read
DESCRIPTION:	Aminet short description ("Short:")
EXECUTE:
REQUIRES:	RexxMast running, 'rx' in command path.
AUTHOR:		Mikael Lund
NOTES:

@{b}Txt@{ub}

FILETYPE:	Textfiles
PATTERN:	(#?.txt|#?.doc|#?.nfo)
PROPERTIES:	Read, Write, Delete, Execute
DESCRIPTION:	File_ID.DIZ
EXECUTE:	Read file using either Dopus5+, Multiview, Amigaguide
		or More.
REQUIRES:	Textract by dRm! / 100%
AUTHOR:		Mikael Lund
NOTES:		"Textract" is available in different 680x0 version,
		install one that fits your processor.

@{b}UUe@{ub}

FILETYPE:	UUencoded archives.
PATTERN:	#?.uue
PROPERTIES:	Read, write, delete, Execute
DESCRIPTION:	File_id.diz
EXECUTE:	Unpack archive.
REQUIRES:	UUArc v1.3 by Miss J.G.Brandon
AUTHOR:		Mikael Lund
NOTES:

@{b}Zip@{ub}

FILETYPE:	ZIP archives.
PATTERN:	#?.zip
PROPERTIES:	Read, write, delete & execute
DESCRIPTION:	file_id.diz
EXECUTE:	Unpack archive.
REQUIRES:	Zip, UnZip, C:Requestfile (OS39+)
AUTHOR:		Mikael Lund
NOTES:		Some ZIP executables can be unstable.

@{b}xFX@{ub}

FILETYPE:	xFX disk-images.
PATTERN:	(#?.xfx)
PROPERTIES:	Read, Write, Delete, Execute
DESCRIPTION:	File_ID.DIZ
EXECUTE:	Unpack to a device, selected by user.
REQUIRES:	ENV:ViewDiz/Modules/Xpk
		xFX by Alessandro Pedretti (aminet)
AUTHOR:		Mikael Lund
NOTES:		xFX is FAR more cool than DMS !

@{b}Xpk@{ub}

FILETYPE:	XPK-packed files.
PATTERN:	(#?.xpk)
PROPERTIES:	Read, Write, Delete, Execute
DESCRIPTION:	File_ID.DIZ
EXECUTE:	Unpack file, overwrites the old one. 
REQUIRES:	xpkmaster.library
		xDiz by Dexter/Abyss
		xUP (For unpacking, only)
AUTHOR:		Mikael Lund
NOTES:		ViewDiz will also detect xpk-files with no .xpk
		suffix.

@{b}Tar@{ub}

FILETYPE:	TAR archive
PATTERN:	#?.tar
PROPERTIES:	Read, write, delete, execute
DESCRIPTION:	file_id.diz
EXECUTE:	Unarchive to user-defined destination.
REQUIRES:	GNU tar, Requestfile (AmigaOS v38+)
AUTHOR:		Mikael Lund
NOTES:

@{b}Tgz@{ub}

FILETYPE:	GZip packed TAR-archive
PATTERN:	#?.targz|#?.tgz|#?.gz
PROPERTIES:	Read, write, delete, execute
DESCRIPTION:	file_id.diz
EXECUTE:	Unpack and unarchive TAR-file
REQUIRES:	GZip 1.2.4+, Env:ViewDiz/Modules/Tar
AUTHOR:		Mikael Lund
NOTES:		GZip can be unstable at low memory configurations.

@{b}Exe@{ub}

FILETYPE:	Executable file
PATTERN:	#?.exe
PROPERTIES:	RWXD
DESCRIPTION:	file_id.diz
EXECUTE:	Run file
REQUIRES:	EXEDescript v1.0 By Remo (Mystic/X-DeSign)
AUTHOR:		Mikael Lund
NOTES:		You should use this only on demos and the like.

@{b}GZip@{ub}

FILETYPE:	GunZip packed file
PATTERN:	#?.gzip|#?.gz
PROPERTIES:	XD
DESCRIPTION:	filenote
EXECUTE:	Unpack file
REQUIRES:	gzip
AUTHOR:		Mikael Lund
@endnode

;---------
@node "wrap"
FUNCTION

   Wrap description to a certain line-width

REQUIRES

   "Wordwrap" by Wilhelm Nöker (Tested with v2.2)

USAGE

   Wrap WIDTH/K

   Default width is 45.

AUTHOR

   Mikael Lund
@endnode
;---------
@node "guidelist"
FUNCTION

   Create an interactive Amigaguide-filelist much like the ones
   that comes with the Aminet CD's.

REQUIRES

   - RexxMast running
   - Rexxdossupport.library

USAGE

   Guidelist GUIDEFILE/K,TITLE/K

   GUIDEFILE/K  Output file to create/add to.
                Default is "Ram:Guidelist.guide"

   TITLE/K      Windowtitle of guide to be created.
                Default is "Guidelist-Wizard Output:"


   The created guide will contain the filename, size, date and the
   description. The filename will be highlighted, and when clicked on,
   viewdiz will be started with the "EXECUTE" switch. This means that
   an archive will be extracted, music will be played etc...

NOTE

   Not completely finished yet.

RESTRICTIONS

   Due to a restriction in the Amigaguide format, it is not possible
   to have spaces in the filename. This is automatically handled.

AUTHOR

   Mikael Lund
@endnode

;---------
@node "banner"
FUNCTION

   Add a textfile to the description - either in top or bottom.

USAGE

   Banner BANNER/K,BOTTOM/S,FRESH/S

   BANNER/K  - Banner to add
   BOTTOM/S  - Add to bottom of description. Default is in top
   FRESH/S   - Replace entire description

   Example:

     ViewDiz Ram:MyFile.lha "Banner BANNER=Ram:Banner.txt"

AUTHOR

   Niels Van Willigenburg
   Mikael Lund
@endnode

;---------
@node "clip"
FUNCTION

   Copies description to Clipboard.

REQUIRES

   - Copy2Clip by Nick Christie (ViewDiz-extras.lha)
   - Or Clip-handler by Michal Letowski (aminet/util/misc/cliphan_1_2.lha)

USAGE

   Clip UNIT/N

   UNIT/N - Clipboard unit to use, default is 0.
            (Not available with Clip-handler)

AUTHOR

   Mikael Lund
@endnode

;---------
@node "dldcheck"
FUNCTION

   Remove banners from Lha-files (without asking!). If the file isn't
   in the Lha-format, the function is skipped.

REQUIRES

   - DLDchecker 4.1+ by Rasmus K. Ursem

USAGE

   DLDcheck

AUTHOR

   Mikael Lund
@endnode
;---------
@node "strip"
FUNCTION

   Strips description for strange chars (ANSI graphics!). Lines
   will be word-wrapped to a linelength of max. 44 chars.

REQUIRES

   RexxMast running
   Sys:RexxC in command path

USAGE

   Strip

AUTHOR

   Niels Van Willigenburg
   Mikael Lund
@endnode
;---------
@node "delreadme"
FUNCTION

   Delete companion .readme file of current file. This is usefull when
   converting aminet descriptions to file_id.diz.

USAGE

   DelReadme

   Example:

     ViewDiz myfile.lha autosave quiet "delreadme"

     - will save the obtained description as file_id.diz and then try to
     delete "myfile.readme" afterwards.

AUTHOR

   Mikael Lund
@endnode

;---------
@node "log"
FUNCTION

   Create a logfile of processed files.

USAGE

   Log NODATE/S,NOPATH/S,FIDLEN/S,LOGFILE

   NODATE/S  Exclude date information
   FIDLEN/S  Include length of description
   NOPATH/S  Exclude path-part ot the filename
   LOGFILE   Specify output logfile - default is "t:ViewDiz_log"

   Example:

     ViewDiz myfile.lha "Log fidlen nopath"

     - adds the following to "t:ViewDiz_log" :
       (Friday 25-Sep-98 17:27:30) 409   "myfile.lha"

   FidLen/S is usefull when searching for files without description.

AUTHOR

   Mikael Lund
@endnode
